South Korean Students Demand Abolition of NSL 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The south Korean National Council of Girl Student Representatives reportedly issued a statement demanding the abolition of the National Security Law (NSL) on December 1.
 Recalling that the law had served as a means of checking the democratization of society and reunification and maintaining the power of the anti-democratic forces since its inception, the statement said its repeal would be the first step toward independent reunification and the beginning of democracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Grand National Party, which is still crying out for the maintenance of the NSL, will face a judgment by history and the Uri Party should clearly know that the abolition of the NSL is the only way of cleansing history of its stain, the statement stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The East Kyonggi Regional Federation of University Student Councils under the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils in its statement on November 30 called upon the youth and students to turn out as one in the struggle to get the NSL totally scrapped within this year.

Thorough Probe into Truth behind Secret Nuclear Development in S. Korea Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korean Committee for Solidarity with the World People in a statement Sunday called upon the peace-loving people of the world and international bodies and organizations to lift up louder voices demanding a thorough probe into the truth behind the secret nuclear development of south Korea and a total stop to it.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently, the International Atomic Energy Agency covered up south Korea's secret experiments of nuclear substances under the manipulation of the United States. This stripped bare once again the true colors of the U.S. which is resorting to high-handed, outrageous and unilateral practices without hesitation, styling itself a police officer and a judge in the international arena, and the ugly sight of the IAEA which has been reduced to a dyed-in-the-wool servant of the U.S. paying no heed to justice, impartiality, international law and world opinion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear development of south Korea which has been carried on for decades with the patronage of the U.S. was obviously based on the latter's nuclear war strategy and it poses a grave threat to the peace on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of the world and the destiny of the Korean nation and the security of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon the world people aspiring after independence and peace to unite and resolutely reject any attempt to turn the world into a unipolar world dominated by the U.S.

Certificate on Registration of Kimjongilia as New Variety of Begonia Family Displayed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- A certificate on the registration of immortal flower Kimjongilia as a new variety of the begonia family at the International Society for Horticultural Science (ISHS) and other new materials were put on display at the Kimilsungia - Kimjongilia Exhibition standing on the bank of the Taedong River here.
 The Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee put on display at the Immortal Flower Information Room of the exhibition the certificate which says the U.S. Begonia Society formally registered Kimjongilia as a new variety No. 991, authorized by the ISHS, a copy of the magazine of the society and a ribbon symbolic of the first place awarded to Kimjongilia at the Begonia Show held in the U.S. recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The magazine introduces the biological characteristics of the flower, stressing that the flower goes by the august name of Kim Jong Il, the great leader of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also carries an article saying that the flower was awarded top prizes at the 12th International Flower Show and the China 99 Kunming World Horticultural Expo as well as a photo of the flower in full bloom.

Extraordinary Meeting of Co-Chairmen of Pomminryon Presidium Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- An extraordinary meeting of the co-chairmen of the Presidium of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) was held on Dec. 5 by fax among the co-chairmen in the north, the south and abroad.
 Discussed at the meeting were immediate tasks facing the Pomminryon organizations.
 There was introduced, to begin with, the joint press release made public at the working-level contact of representatives of Koreans from the north, the south and overseas held in Mt. Kumgang on Nov. 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special resolution titled "Let us make significant 2005 the year of independent reunification by upholding and carrying through the June 15 joint declaration" was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution reviewed the brilliant successes achieved in the north, the south and overseas in the movement for national reunification in 2004.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Stating that Pomminryon would make every possible effort to make significant 2005 the year of independent reunification and the year of the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea, it said: To this end, national cooperation should be definitely realized under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration and the anti-U.S. movement for the reunification of the country be waged on a nation-wide scale against the U.S. moves for a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying the Songun force of the north is a force of the nation to prevent a war on the Korean Peninsula and defend the nation, the resolution called for waging a nation-wide struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces, the principal criminal seeking a war on the peninsula, by pooling the Songun force of the north and the force against the U.S. and for independence in the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a practical step, we will form "the North-South Joint Measure Committee for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Forces" at an early date to launch into the struggle for making 2005 practically the year of the withdrawal of the U.S. forces and will successfully hold a national joint function marking the 5th anniversary of the publication of the joint declaration and an August 15 reunification function as grand national festivals for reunification while striving to strengthen national cooperation, the resolution declared. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It underlined the need to make vehement efforts to have Pomminryon legalized through the abolition of the "National Security Law" and further develop the nationwide movement for reunification by realizing three-party cooperation on a high level and hold the 9th meeting of the co-chairmen of the Pomminryon Presidium with the gathering of those in the north, the south and abroad at one place next year.

Year of Epochal Significance in DPRK-China Friendship
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- This is a historic year in which the DPRK-China friendship has strengthened still further.
 The unofficial visit of leader Kim Jong Il to China in April marked a new milestone in the development of the bilateral friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the visit, he met and had talks with Hu Jintao. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks, held in a cordial and friendly atmosphere, the two leaders exchanged their views and reached a consensus on the issue of further developing the relations between the two parties and two countries and important international issues of common concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deeply rooted friendship between the DPRK and China has been carried forward by their leaders through generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung, along with Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai and Deng Xiaoping, provided the historic foundation of the DPRK-China friendship and developed it with a strong sense of revolutionary obligation and fraternity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's unofficial visit demonstrated the steadfast will of the Workers' Party and government of Korea to further develop the friendship with China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mutual visits of high-level delegations of the two countries this year have further cemented the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A DPRK delegation headed by Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, paid an official goodwill visit to China in October which marked  the 55th anniversary of the opening of the diplomatic relations between the two countries. This once again demonstrated the invariable stand of the Party and government of Korea to carry forward the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A delegation of the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China led by Wang Jiarui, head of the department visited the DPRK in January, Chinese Foreign Minister Li Zhaoxing and his party in March and a party and government delegation of China headed by Li Changchun, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the C.C., CPC, in September. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The two countries also exchanged delegations of various levels in the political, economic, military and cultural fields, deepening the bilateral friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese government has donated the Taean Friendship Glass Factory and other things to the DPRK this year.

Anti-U.S. Sentiments Grow Stronger in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- Anti-U.S. sentiments are growing stronger among the people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The U.S. imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK under the groundless pretext of "nuclear", "human rights" and "religious" issues have enraged the Korean servicemen and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, after working out "Operation Plan 5027-04", a new war scenario against the DPRK, are now intensifying blackmail and pressure on it. This only makes the Korean people's anti-U.S. sentiments stronger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large number of people visit museums which house materials and relics showing brutalities committed by the U.S. imperialists in the country during the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are the Sinchon Museum in South Hwanghae Province and the monument to the sinking of the U.S. aggression ship "General Sherman" and its armed spy ship "Pueblo" on the River Taedong flowing through Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
All the exhibits disclose in all nakedness that the U.S. imperialists have perpetrated all manner of crimes against the Korean nation through centuries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, mass media frequently edit articles condemning the U.S. imperialists as the arch enemy of the Korean people and televise films exposing their blood-stained history of aggression.
